snippet: Defense Minister Ehud Barak said that Israeli and Palestinian negotiators exchanged position papers at a meeting this week, but neither side held out the promise of a breakthrough.
abstract: Israeli Defense Minister Ehud Barak says that Israeli and Palestinian negotiators exchanged position papers in Amman, Jordan, during the first direct discussion between the sides in more than 15 months, but neither holds out the promise of a breakthrough.
lead_paragraph: Defense Minister Ehud Barak said that Israeli and Palestinian negotiators exchanged position papers at a meeting this week, but neither side held out the promise of a breakthrough.

headline.seo: Israelis and Palestinians Exchange Position Papers, and Talks Will Resume
